			<abstract>
				<p>Testimony of B.B. and B.J., both 24, on anti-Jewish atrocities in Munkács/Mukačevo before and after the German occupation,
					including the desecration of the synagogue on the so-called “Black Sabbath” in the spring of 1944, the ghetto and transit camp in
					Munkács, deportation to Auschwitz, selection and slave labor, transports to Bergen-Belsen, Weisswasser, and Horneburg, forced
					labor in armament factories, their re-union in Bergen-Belsen, and liberation in Celle.</p>
			</abstract>
		</profileDesc>
